From: Juniper Bevensee <juniperbevensee@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 22 May 2026 22:39:05 +1200
Subject: [PATCH 09/27] feat(swarm-map-policy): session context caching, admin
 resolution, and approval gating

Implements MT Phase 1, Tasks 1-3:

1. Session context caching via pre_gateway_dispatch hook:
   - Uses threading.local() to cache platform/chat_id/user_id/is_admin
   - Extracts from MessageEvent.source on each incoming message
   - Exposes get_session_context() and clear_session_context() helpers

2. Admin identity resolution from HSM API:
   - Calls is_platform_admin() during pre_gateway_dispatch
   - Caches result in thread-local is_admin flag
   - Fail-closed: defaults to False on any error

3. Approval command admin gating via pre_tool_call:
   - ADMIN_GATED_TOOLS set blocks "approval" and "pr_approval"
   - Returns {"action": "block"} for non-admin users
   - Fail-closed: blocks if no session context exists

15 new tests covering all three features (22 total, all passing).

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context) <noreply@anthropic.com>
